Author: whaleterweight
Text: I've been on various types of birth control since I was 11 years old. There's an adjustment period when you start a new prescription while your body adjusts to the changing hormones. It can take a couple of months for things to really settle down and for you to get an idea if it is working well for you. Then, it can take some trial and error to find the right form for you.
